These scripts launch hunchentoot as a daemon at startup under FreeBSD
7.2 behind Apache via mod_proxy.
* you need to create the user htoot
which runs the web server.  Its home directory is /var/lib/hunchentoot
and have no login shell.
* place the file core.lisp in the directory /var/lib/hunchentoot and
the file hunchentoot in /etc/rc.d
* as root, run sbcl --script core.lisp to create a core file for
hunchentoot
* make sure that the directory /var/lib/hunchentoot is readable and
executable only by htoot and that this user owns all the file under this
directory.
* add the entry hunchentoot_enable="YES" in /etc/rc.conf